-- Spanish Interest Rates Raise Concern, Italy’s Monti Says
-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 2012-03-24T16:35:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/spanish-interest-rates-raise-concern-italy-s-monti-says.html
Spain  is raising concerns among its
European neighbors with increasing interest rates,  Italy ’s Prime
Minister  Mario Monti  said.  “Spain has done a very incisive labor reform, but hasn’t
paid enough attention on its public accounts,” Monti said at a
conference in Cernobbio, Italy, today. “It doesn’t take much to
recreate risks of contagion.”   To contact the reporter on this story:
